│                                                                                        │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                        │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                            │
│ The transformation in foldIsPowerOf2 replaces a guarded use of the ctpop result with   │
│ an unguarded use. In the source IR, ctpop has range metadata range(i32 1, 33), which   │
│ excludes 0. That metadata means the ctpop value is poison if it is 0. The source uses  │
│ a select with condition (x != 0) to guard the use of ctpop: when x==0, the ctpop value │
│ (which would be 0) is not used, so poison does not propagate. InstCombine folds the    │
│ pattern (x != 0) && (ctpop(x) u< 2) to (ctpop(x) == 1), removing the guard and using   │
│ ctpop unconditionally. If x==0, ctpop==0, but the metadata says it must be in [1,32],  │
│ so the ctpop value becomes poison at use, making the transformed IR more poisonous     │
│ than the source.                                                                       │
│                                                                                        │
